I made this soup last week when I got sick. Really enjoyed it; good for when you want something warm but don‚Äôt can‚Äôt eat a lot in one sitting. https://warpcast.com/lama/0xed48f8ff

Ingredients:
- onion
- green onion
- garlic
- ginger
- chicken stock
- bell peppers
- celery
- enoki mushrooms
- coriander seeds, cumin

1. Toast the spices (also toss in a dried hot pepper if available)
2. Add olive oil and throw in onion, green onion (white part only), ginger, and garlic
3. Add celery
4. Add bell peppers
5. Add enoki mushrooms
6. Add chicken stock and cover. If you don‚Äôt want it spicy, remove the hot pepper before adding the stock

And for the love of God, SALT YOUR FOOD

I like to taste after every step and salt accordingly
